definition.value: A member of the class of bipyridines that is 2,3'-bipyridin-6'-one substituted at positions 1' and 5' by phenyl and 2-cyanophenyl groups respectively. Used as an adjunctive therapy for the treatment of partial-onset seizures in patients with epilepsy.
An antagonist at the AMPA receptor.
A hydrate obtained by combining four molecules of perampanel with three molecules of water. Used as an adjunctive therapy for the treatment of partial-onset seizures in patients with epilepsy.
A hexahydroxy steroidal lactone obtained by hydrolysis of ouabain.
A hydroxy steroid having a hydroxy group located at position 1.
An N-acylglycine that is the 4-hydroxy derivative of hippuric acid.
A cephalotaxine-derived alkaloid ester obtained from Cephalotaxus harringtonia; used for the treatment of chronic or accelerated phase chronic myeloid leukaemia.
A cardenolide glycoside that is the 16-acetate of gitoxin.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of 15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine-1-phosphocholine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino function; major species at pH 7.3.
A cardenolide glycoside that is the 3-(6-deoxy-3-O-methyl-alpha-L-taloside) of 1beta,3beta,14-trihydroxy-5beta-card-20(22)-enolide.

An imidazobenzazepine that is 6,11-dihydro-5H-imidazo[2,1-b][3]benzazepine substituted at position 3 by a formyl group and at position 11 by a 1-methylpiperidin-4-ylidene group. An antihistamine used for treatment of allergic conjunctivitis.
Any organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of an imidazole ring ortho-fused to a benzazepine.

A 20-oxo steroid obtained by acetylation of the 17-hydroxy group of (11beta,17alpha)-17-acetyl-11-[4-(dimethylamino)phenyl]-3-oxoestra-4,9-dien-17-ol (ulipristal). A selective progesterone receptor modulator, which is employed as an emergency  contraceptive.
Indole-3-acetic acid substituted on nitrogen with a 4-chlorobenzoyl group and at C-5 by a methoxy group.
A hormone receptor modulator that acts as a complete or partial agonist or as an antagonist at the progesterone receptor.
A urea that is the N-carbamoyl derivative of L-glutamic acid. An orphan drug used to treat a deficiency in the enzyme N-acetylglutamate synthase, which leads to acute hyperammonaemia.
A dipeptide that is the N-(L-seryl) derivative of L-phenylalanine.
An anionic phospholipid that is the conjugate base of 15-methylhexadecasphinganine 1-phosphate, having an anionic phosphate group and a protonated amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Any drug that has been developed specifically for treatment of a rare medical condition, the condition itself being known as an orphan disease.
A dipeptide that is the N-(L-phenylalanyl) derivative of L-serine.
Any compound that binds and activates the enzyme carbamylphosphate synthetase I.
A fatty aldehyde consisting of tetradecanal substituted at position 13 by a methyl group.

A branched amino decasaccharide comprised of a linear hexasaccharide chain of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, alpha-D-mannose, beta-D-mannose, and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4), (1->2), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4), to the beta-D-mannose residue of which is (1->6)-linked an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl side-chain.
A phosphosphigolipid that is 15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine bearing a single phospho substituent at position 1.
Any flavonoid with one or more rings fused on to the phenyl substituted benzopyran  framework.
An acyl-CoA that results from formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the 1-carboxy group of 3-hydroxyadipic acid.

A linear amino hexasaccharide comprised of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, alpha-D-mannose, beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4), (1->2), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4).

A linear amino hexasaccharide comprised of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, alpha-D-mannose, beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4), (1->2), (1->6), (1->4) and (1->4).
A sphingoid obtained by formal oxidation of the 3-hydroxy group of hexadecasphinganine.

A branched hexasaccharide consisting of a linear sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-mannose and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues linked (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4), to the galactose residue of which is (1->6)-linked a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl disaccharide unit.
A sphingoid obtained by formal oxidation of the 3-hydroxy group of tetradecasphinganine.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 2,3-didehydroadipoyl-CoA.
A beta-diketone that is methane in which two of the hydrogens are substituted by 4-hydroxycinnamoyl groups.
A sphingoid obtained by formal hydrogenation of the C=C bond of tetradecasphingosine
An arenesulfonic acid that is phenol substituted by a sulfo group at C-3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (S)-dihydrocamalexic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
An arenesulfonic acid that is phenol substituted by a sulfo group at C-2.
A sphingoid obtained by formal hydrogenation of the C=C bond of hexadecasphingosine.

A branched pentasaccharide consisting of a linear sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-mannose and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues linked (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4), to the galactose residue of which is (1->6)-linked an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue.
A sphingoid that is the C16 analogue of sphingosine.
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of a chain of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3).
beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc with alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre of the reducing-end GalNAc residue.
A linear amino tetrasaccharide consisting of a sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked (1->4), (1->3) and (1->3).
A phosphosphingolipid that is 15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine substituted at position 1 by a phosphocholine moiety
An N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as 3-pyridylacetyl.

A branched amino octasaccharide comprised of a sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine,beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues, linked (1->4), (1->3), (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4), to the reducing-end and centrally positioned GlcNAc residues of which are also (1->3)-linked alpha-L-fucose residues.
A phosphosphingolipid that is 15-methylhexadecasphinganine bearing a single phospho substituent at position 1.
An octasaccharide derivative having one or more substituted or unsubstituted amino groups in place of hydroxy groups at unspecified positions.
An oligosaccharide derivative that is formally obtained from an octasaccharide.
